						<summary>

						<p>Left wall of the entrance of the <hi rend="italic">gōpura</hi> in the Aiyaṉār temple.</p>						

						<p>This inscription engraved in characters of about the 13th century A.D, states that this <hi rend="italic">gōpura</hi> was caused to be constructed by Teṟṟi Ādittaṉ <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Ottaga[ne]rittap-pichchaṉ of Tiru Āyappāḍi-nāḍu. </p>						

